                </p>

                <p>
                    The line that bisects an angle is called an angle bisector.
                </p>
             </statement>
         </activity>

            <example>
                <statement>
                    <p>
                        If an angle bisector divides an angle of <m>120</m> degrees, then what is the measure of each angle?
                    </p>

                </statement>
            </example>

                <solution>
                    <p>
                        Given, a measure of an angle is <m>120</m> degrees
                    </p>

                    <p>
                        As we know, the angle bisector divides the angle into equal two parts.
                    </p>

                    <p>
                        Therefore, <m>120</m> degrees is divided into equal two parts, say <m>x</m>.
                    </p>

                    <p>
                        Hence,
                    </p>

                    <p>
                        <me>
                            x + x = 120°
                        </me>    
                    </p>

                    <p>
                        <me>
                            2x = 120°
                        </me>  
                    </p>

                    <p>
                        <me>
                            x = \frac{120^}{2}
                        </me>     
                    </p>

                    <p>
                        <me>
                        x=60^\circ 
                        </me>      
                    </p>
                </solution>

